Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: VirusBay is a web-based collaboration platform with relevant malware researchers. It is designed to help organizations effectively respond to and recover from an IT security incident when it is not possible for an external expert to visit their facility. In return, the researcher gains access to malware samples for analysis to improve detection for all. The ultimate goal of VirusBay is to build a community of expertise and data sharing. Description: An integrated cloud-based platform that facilitates the search, selection and management of a business’ external workforce.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Their story begins over a cup of coffee and a long discussion about providers.  They were sharing stories and advice on their experience working with various service and solution providers. Now by providers, they mean those businesses that provide solutions and services for other businesses such as printing, marketing, graphic design, web development, and strategy, just to name a few.  In their past lives working in everything between startups and Fortune 50 companies, they collaborated quite a bit with these various providers.  They found that some were extremely good across the board, quite a few were pretty good but often in one area vs all of the services they advertised, and some that were just plain…well, awful.   They found that along the way, one of their greatest challenges, was the ability to simply locate a top provider that was exceptional for the project they need fulfilled – you know - someone that produced consistent high-quality work, communicated in a timely manner, stuck to timelines and most importantly, “WOW’ed” us with the end result.   The problem is that when you’re looking for a provider, often times, its guesswork.  You either base your decision on the top search results by a Search Engine, word-of-mouth advice from others, random online reviews, a sales pitch by a rep or most likely, blind faith.  So, they figured that there had to be a better way to capture these “conversations”, improve one’s ability to find and select providers to meet their day-to-day needs, and in doing so drive the “economy” of how businesses work with providers.      And thus a single conversation, became the start of a two-year journey to come up with an ideal solution that would simplify this entire provider selection and management process, equipping businesses with the necessary resources and information to find the right providers for their business.

Full Description: Jobe Consulting Group, LLC (JCG) is a multi-disciplinary, minority, woman-owned professional services company that has been providing services to federal government, state and local governments, and commercial customers for over eight years. We provide services in four core business arenas; Management Consulting, Education and Training Consulting, Business Development Consulting, and Environmental Consulting.   In early 2008, Jobe Consulting Group, LLC launched into a new business arena and started its Property Development Consulting business area.  This business area provides project management, construction management, marketing, preliminary design and planning, and construction engineering consulting services to its commercial clients. Our business model is predicated on taking advantage of the available low acreage lots that are close to and inside the District of Columbia border that are typically ignored by most real estate developers.  By consolidating these lots and developing what we call energy positive single family homes we will create a niche market  and deliver exceptional value and product quality to the marketplace.  The lots range in size from a low of 0.11 acres to a high of1.5 acres and are all zoned R-60.  The market differentiator for these new construction homes will be the integration of eco-friendly and energy efficient components into the design and build of each home. These components will include, but not be limited to:  Photovoltaic (solar) energy systems and/or wind energy systems; Natural Gas power cell generator energy systems; Geo-thermal heating/cooling systems; Sustainably-sourced wood flooring (primarily use bamboo).  It is our intent to create a new company once we have procured funding and are offering 40% equity ownership in that new entity.  Minimum investment is $5,000 and projected returns will range from 15 to 25 % per annum.
